    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to caps or hoodlike devices which cover and protect the open top of pipes, stacks, or shafts while permitting the free passage of air.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000077471/Sturgis, Dictionary of Architecture and Building (1901)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a tapas o elementos como capuchas los cuales cubren y protegen la apertura superior de tubos, cañón de chimeneas, o pozos mientras permiten el pase libre del aire.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
